      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a common concern, but research shows it's more nuanced. Small businesses often have a local community focus and may not have the scale of financial reserves that larger corporations do. While some businesses might struggle during an economic change, many are nimble enough to adapt. Diversifying products or services and staying engaged with your community can actually be a strength. Collectively, local economies can benefit from initiatives like a higher minimum wage if businesses adjust wisely. It's not a one-size-fits-all; it depends on the individual business's strategy and adaptability.",
